Mark Tovey says doctors are satisfied with the progress he's made and he could be discharged soon. JOHANNESBURG Neil Tovey's family has thanked the public for the support and well wishes since he was admitted to hospital. The Safa technical director suffered a heart attack during training and was rushed to hospital a week ago where he was placed in intensive care. His brother, Mark Tovey says doctors are satisfied with the progress he's made and he could be discharged soon. We wanted to say to the public thank you for all your prayers and he pulled through this challenging exercise.